[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm diving into the Native Image compile and whether it includes classworlds. I wonder if there's a resource I might have missed. I need to catch an error for unsupported scenarios, but dynamic class loading isn't open-ended here. The Bootstrapper allows dynamic loading from an embedded jar, though my test uses a fixed class. It looks like the InitialClassLoader is scanning resources which could lead to a potential NullPointerException instead of an unsupported error. I’m considering various ways to manipulate the class and test resources, but there seem to be conflicts I need to think through carefully.
