ng about JVM modules and wondering if sun.misc.Unsafe is included in jdk.unsupported. It looks like privateLookupIn may fail unless the sun.misc module is opened to unnamed modules. I know that reflection’s setAccessible method works, so I’m checking existing implementations. To avoid using field offset, I might consider a Plan B with two tests. I need to ensure the current public constructor for JVM coverage is sufficient if the native approach fails.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering save options**\\n\\nI need to save both states before anything else. The InitialClassLoader constructor might set `classworlds.lib`, so I should restore that afterward. There’s a chance that `classworlds.bootstrapped` was saved after the construction, but that seems fine for now. I think the best plan is to edit the code to ensure I save before the constructor runs and then restore both elements afterward. That way, everything should work smoothly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ByJUYqxYBuU0ukBeFanwDhxO|fc_0f42888f5d5a65d60169fb9e532c888191bf98ca487f9f96cd", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/classworlds/classworlds/1.1/src/test/java/classworlds/classworlds/BootstrapperTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        BootstrapApplication.reset();\n        RecordingClassLoader classLoader = new RecordingClassLoader();\n        TestBootstrapper bootstrapper = new TestBootstrapper(new String[] {\"alpha\", \"beta\"}, classLoader);\n        String previousBootstrapped = System.getProperty(\"classworlds.bootstrapped\");\n        try {\n            System.clearProperty(\"classworlds.bootstrapped\");\n\n            bootstrapper.bootstrap();\n\n            assertThat(classLoader.loadedClassName).isEqualTo(Bootstrapper.LAUNCHER_CLASS_NAME);\n            assertThat(System.getProperty(\"classworlds.bootstrapped\")).isEqualTo(\"true\");\n            assertThat(BootstrapApplication.arguments).containsExactly(\"alpha\", \"beta\");\n        } finally {\n        